The '''black-bibbed tit''' ('''''Poecile hypermelaenus''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the tit family [[tit (bird)|Paridae]].<ref name="harrap">{{Cite book  | last = Harrap  | first = S. |author2=Quinn, D. | title = Tits, Nuthatches and Treecreepers | publisher = Christopher Helm  | year = 1996  | isbn = 0-7136-3964-4}}</ref> It is found from central and eastern [[China]] to southeast [[Tibet]] and western [[Myanmar]].

